Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{}, pop back in the pan, cover with a lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Thinly slice the @Portobello Mushrooms{3}(thinly sliced) into 1cm slices.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped).

Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}(roughly chopped).

Chop the @TenderstemÂź Broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot add the mushroom and TenderstemÂź to the pan, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden, stirring occasionally, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of oil to the pan if needed.

Once the mushroom and broccoli are cooked, stir through the @Bulgogi Sauce{150%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and a squeeze of lime juice. Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the rice has cooked, fluff up with a #fork{} and stir the lime zest in.

Divide the rice between #bowls{} and top with the mushrooms mix.

Sprinkle over the spring onion, peanuts and chilli.

> TIP: Add less chilli if you don't like too much heat.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!